      "swell_gap_basis": "LiPo pouch cells swell ~8-10 percent in thickness over life; for a 5.6 mm cell that is ~0.45-0.56 mm. The device thickness was raised from 11.8 to 12.7 mm purely to open a defined >=0.6 mm swell void on the battery BACK face (toward the back shell, away from the display) so swell never pushes the display. The void is a real air gap between the battery back face (Z=-4.6 mm) and the back inner wall (Z=-5.2 mm); a compressible foam pad occupies the back-shell side of the void with 0.18 mm documented compression allowance, absorbing the arithmetic worst-case tolerance overage without preloading the cell. The display-side gap stays the static 0.15 mm minimum so the cell cannot crack the panel under swell.",
