        "purpose": "Aperture/band-switch tuner that retunes the electrically-small low-band element across 700-960 MHz. The radio matches only one ~20 MHz carrier at a time, so the modem programs the tuner state to center the Chu-limited match window on the active channel. Each state's instantaneous carrier bandwidth fits the Chu cap and the state grid step stays inside the match window (no coverage gap), resolving the whole-band shortfall (31.7% span vs 8.4% Chu instantaneous BW). Modeled in simulate_e1_phone_rf_si_pi.py; verdict PASS_WITH_TUNER, worst-state total efficiency ~-3.1 dB after 0.5 dB tuner IL.",
